# ===== Node globals =====
# NOTE: deliberately NO `npm "..."` entries. `brew bundle dump` on the old Mac
# captured claude-code BOTH as a cask (above) and as an npm global, plus corepack.
# On a fresh Mac those double-installs collide and fail `brew bundle`:
#   - npm "@anthropic-ai/claude-code" -> EEXIST on /opt/homebrew/bin/claude (cask owns it)
#   - npm "corepack"                  -> EEXIST on /opt/homebrew/bin/pnpm  (brew pnpm owns it)
# claude-code is provided by the cask above; corepack already ships with Node.
# Run `corepack enable` by hand if you ever want the pnpm/yarn shims.
